[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-06-16 20:37:44.000000000', 'files': ['glance/tests/unit/test_notifier.py', 'glance/notifier.py'], 'message': "notifier: simply notifier_strategy compat support

In order to handle the deprecated notifier_strategy configuration option
we just need to translate the notifier_strategy value as follows:

  default -> transport_url=None, driver='noop'
  noop -> transport_url=None, driver='noop'
  logging -> transport_url=None, driver='log'
  rabbit -> transport_url=rabbit:///, driver='messaging'
  qpid -> transport_url=qpid:///, driver='messaging'
  None -> transport_url=None, driver=None

where the last bit simply means that the user hasn't specified any
notifier_strategy and we should just have oslo.messaging load a notifier
based on oslo.messaging's config options.

It really doesn't need to be any more complicated than that, and we
certainly shouldn't need to poke at what the user may have configured
for transport_url in their config file.

The reason this is important is that CONF.transport_url is a private
configuration option which soon will not be visible to users of the
oslo.messaging API. See I9c3bf74f13a820ce295aa77a2bbcd781778b5926.

Also, simplify the testing of this stuff by mocking the oslo.messaging
APIs used and using the test scenarios outlined above. This also means
we stop poking around in oslo.messaging internals like:

       self.assertEqual(str(nfier._transport._driver._url),
                        'qpid:///')

Naughty, naughty!

Note: it's arguable we should just remove notifier_strategy in Juno
since we deprecated it in Icehouse, but this patch will be useful to
backport to stable/icehouse in any case.

Change-Id: I067248974baee50a2a0afb38bf022b65d1bea57a
"}]
commit_message:
notifier: simply notifier_strategy compat support

In order to handle the deprecated notifier_strategy configuration option
we just need to translate the notifier_strategy value as follows:

  default -> transport_url=None, driver='noop'
  noop -> transport_url=None, driver='noop'
  logging -> transport_url=None, driver='log'
  rabbit -> transport_url=rabbit:///, driver='messaging'
  qpid -> transport_url=qpid:///, driver='messaging'
  None -> transport_url=None, driver=None

where the last bit simply means that the user hasn't specified any
notifier_strategy and we should just have oslo.messaging load a notifier
based on oslo.messaging's config options.

It really doesn't need to be any more complicated than that, and we
certainly shouldn't need to poke at what the user may have configured
for transport_url in their config file.

The reason this is important is that CONF.transport_url is a private
configuration option which soon will not be visible to users of the
oslo.messaging API. See I9c3bf74f13a820ce295aa77a2bbcd781778b5926.

Also, simplify the testing of this stuff by mocking the oslo.messaging
APIs used and using the test scenarios outlined above. This also means
we stop poking around in oslo.messaging internals like:

       self.assertEqual(str(nfier._transport._driver._url),
                        'qpid:///')

Naughty, naughty!

Note: it's arguable we should just remove notifier_strategy in Juno
since we deprecated it in Icehouse, but this patch will be useful to
backport to stable/icehouse in any case.

Change-Id: I067248974baee50a2a0afb38bf022b65d1bea57a

commit_message:
Make check_instance_shared_storage() use objects

This changes the check_instance_shared_storage () method in compute manager
to take an instance object.

The change is mostly cosmetic here to remove one more case of an instance dict
being passed by the rpcapi since the instance parameter isn't actually used on
the server end of this call anyway !

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: Id22306916d5d32af978955e02ee95e991c733bab

commit_message:
Hook aggregate API to update aggregate info in compute_nodes

When isolate the scheduler db, We want to save the list of IDs of aggregates
the host belongs to in extra resources as a JSON in compute_nodes table,
the filters can get IDs from the host state, For making sure there is no
crucial latency in between aggregates changes in API and scheduler-related
view, hook the API to call RT for updating host state if hosts are added or
removed from an aggregate.

Co-Authored-By: Sylvain Bauza <sbauza@redhat.com>

Implements: blueprint isolate-scheduler-db
Change-Id: I73e7a542f40c76ba45e9593e03a6bcd3aeb8c2c5

commit_message:
Add helper functions for getting local disk

Following functions are added in order to be used by validate_bdm
and resource_tracker code.
get_bdm_ephemeral_disk_size: return sum of eph disk size of bdms
get_bdm_swap_list: return a swap disk list of bdms
get_bdm_local_disk_num: return local disk number (include eph and swap)

Change-Id: I215970bea72b502042472aa310fe64ffc4304b25

commit_message:
Increased timeout for Heat OSTF test

We had small timeout for Heat stack creation operation
and this commit will fix it to 10 minutes. Heat stack
with small image should be created for this time on any
environments, even with small amount of RAM.

commit_message:
Change the way multiple values for dynamic UI 'type' attr are parsed

* Pass multiple values for 'type' as normal YAML sequence, not string.
* Add emptyValueMessage attribute to such fields. It will be used as a
  description of initial empty value.
* Deprecate 'domain' type - io.murano.windows.ActiveDirectory should be
  used instead (use openstack.common.versionutils.deprecated).

Targets: blueprint dynamic-ui-deprecate-obsolete-fields
Change-Id: I451ce0282910d36b3040a96b2380de348e6bdb53

commit_message:
Add versionutils from oslo to use @deprecated helper

Also run oslo update.py script on murano-dashboard.

Do not use muranodashboard.openstack.common.log (use unstead the same
module from openstack_dashboard), because having 2 different log
modules causes DuplicateOptError exception. This is related to bug 
#1328247.

Updated with oslo-incubator 1cc7390033aa704d150cc3e9724d2a3fabbbe6b6

Change-Id: Ie1c4f1b043c0c55ee9adbfcabe1824c0a5c81f9a

commit_message:
Change Scheduler access to Aggregates

So as to fork the Scheduler code into a separate project, we need to
change the way the Scheduler accesses other Nova objects

This change is only focusing on aggregates.

Regarding accesses to aggregates table, the change can be divided in
three parts:
- modify ResourceTracker update_available_resource so that it provides
  scheduler a list of IDs of aggregates the host belongs to, as a JSON
  in extra resources.
- provide aggregates as part of the request_spec argument of
  select_destinations() when filtering from explicit aggregates or AZs.
- update scheduler filters so that it looks into HostState instead of
  aggregates and gets the associate metadata in request_spec.

Note: no other data except JSON will be changed in compute_nodes.

Co-Authored-By: Sylvain Bauza <sbauza@redhat.com>

Implements: blueprint isolate-scheduler-db
Change-Id: I3bb005f4d3ef74adb992498dd001d13e3fb16387

commit_message:
Remove the unused success_url and return

Since 'Change Password' form handle successfully return
httpResponseRedirect(settings.LOGOUT_URL), it's no need
to set success_url and never reach the 'return True' at
the end.

Change-Id: I47c8888b07d06044fec8f06042d4ef6401e77097
Closes-Bug: #1331329

commit_message:
Add SwiftSortingMethod parameter

This is a second attempt to add the SwiftSortingMethod parameter.
An earlier attempt, https://review.openstack.org/#/c/84470/ was
abandoned because of the significant config and deploy changes.

This parameter is used by swift to determine how
storage nodes are chosen. Valid values are shuffle (choose nodes at random),
timing (by using timing measurements), or affinity (by using an explicit match).

The default SwiftSortingMethod is shuffle.

See https://review.openstack.org/#/c/83323/ for the matching change
required to include the sorting_method attribute in proxy-server.conf
in the swift-proxy image element.

Change-Id: Ide124021cf8e678bf704fa13bdf04b5431155a31

commit_message:
Set include_service_catalog and sorting_method in proxy-server.conf

The swift docs in swift/doc/source/overview_auth.rst recommend setting
include_service_catalog false (it has a default value of true) since Swift
does not use the X-Service-Catalog header, there is no point in getting the
service catalog

The sorting_method attribute is used by swift to determine how
storage nodes are chosen. Valid values are shuffle (choose nodes at random),
timing (by using timing measurements), or affinity (by using an explicit match)

The default sorting_method is shuffle

The SwiftSortingMethod Parameter is defined in the swift-source.yaml
See https://review.openstack.org/#/c/84470/

Change-Id: I3945f98fe3fca3a8e74de798068c3abce5a98d5e

commit_message:
Do not set NeutronControlPlaneID when building image only

When just building image, the NeutronControlPlaneID can't get a value
and the shell will fail, so set NeutronControlPlaneID when BUILD_ONLY
is 0.

Change-Id: I2724b5a6afc7525a5c83a93446d7462c804ab9ca

commit_message:
Cleanup resources with tempest more reliably

In case method setUpClass fails, method tearDownClass
won't run and won't clear resources, it is fixed by
adding decorator to setUpClass with forced run of tearDownClass.
Also moved per-test cleanup from tearDown to setUp method
using addCleanup from testtools module.

Change-Id: Id0e2f42dc1bbf050f534c9439bd7e0b65e966d49

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-06-01 15:12:18.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/api/v2/resource_helper.py'], 'message': 'Fixing resource_helper to prefer extended resource

resource_helper module constructs Controller and ResourceRExtension objects
for extension's resources.

Extension's resources may be expanded by other extensions
and there is a mechanism making it happen on the main resources
repository, api/v2/attributes.RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_MAP.

resource_helper gets the "original" extension's resources as a parameter

and, if it exists, uses it for building Controller object of the resource
instead of using the "original" resource from extension.

Closes-Bug: 1325370

commit_message:
Fixing resource_helper to prefer extended resource

resource_helper module constructs Controller and ResourceRExtension objects
for extension's resources.

Extension's resources may be expanded by other extensions
and there is a mechanism making it happen on the main resources
repository, api/v2/attributes.RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_MAP.

resource_helper gets the "original" extension's resources as a parameter
from the extension itself.
This change tries to get the extended resource from the main repository
and, if it exists, uses it for building Controller object of the resource
instead of using the "original" resource from extension.

Change-Id: I20b5505248fdbf59e31bbfcab5642eccaa2dc8d7
Closes-Bug: 1325370

The install and configuration guide for object storage has
proxy-server.conf contents with /home/swift/keystone-signing as

commit_message:
Corrects proxy server conf in swift install guide

The install and configuration guide for object storage has
proxy-server.conf contents with /home/swift/keystone-signing as
signing directory. Without the directory being available swift proxy
service is unable to start. Signing directory is a temporary cache
directory which defaults to /tmp. Hence removing this entry makes
/tmp as default signing directory. This patch removes signing_dir
option to make swift use /tmp as signing directory implicitly.

Change-Id: I8b9b70b30af2767f48705acb14329833179b96fc
Closes-Bug: #1329798
(cherry picked from commit abed3e59e159136b39a498a013983d0cf9efded9)

commit_message:
Notify systemd when starting Neutron server

systemd is notified only when Neutron is started with multiple api
workers. This patch adds systemd.notify_once() call when starting
Neutron server with api_workers=0

Closes-Bug: #1330532

Conflicts:
	neutron/wsgi.py

Change-Id: I95581dc5dffde6168c68d9f04cf8bdfcdb773ba8

commit_message:
Sync service and systemd modules from oslo-incubator

This patch make systemd know when neutron-service was started. This is
needed in HA environment, previously systemd returned success even
before neutron-server was able to handle requests.

Current oslo-incubator commit on HEAD:
b7ad6ddab8b1d61bf4f52ccaa461a9d68809747b

Implements: blueprint service-readiness
Change-Id: Ic9e4abd11b614a896fbd7454b9a604a69a248d0f
(cherry picked from commit 149679b2dc2e202b37580a3210f3a25628c4339b)

commit_message:
Make exception handling in get_image_metadata more specific

The generic try/except with Exception was masking an
AttributeError raised during migration flows in conductor.

This change makes the error handling specific to the translated
exceptions raised from the image service in nova.image.glance,
specifically the _translate_image_exception method.

Related-Bug: #1326926

Change-Id: I3e4db73569fc1b02d7a05b4ab10fe83fec956922

commit_message:
live migrate conductor tasks to use nova.image.API

While the patch (I67e7c9d841e5bad82cdca8f7048eaa57f0cfbb2f) was being
reviewed, live_migrate functionality was moved to the conductor. This
live_migrate task code needed to be updated to refer to the new
nova.image.API object instead of the old nova.glance.GlanceImageService
object, which had a slightly different API.

commit_message:
Allowing for HDFS data sources without hdfs://

Now that HDFS data sources can be either full URLs
or paths relative to the cluster itself, it is no
longer desirable to force "hdfs://" at the start
of hdfs data sources.
* No longer force the prefix on the create form
* For swift, we now check to see that the location
  starts with swift://, if it doesn't we add it

Change-Id: Id1fcdb741ce702ad194cf86556be2f3f0e8cd049
Partial-Bug:  bug 1315126

commit_message:
enables patch ports when availble for connecting openvswitch bridges

The current implementation for connecting openvswtich bridges
when when not using vxlan or gre tunnels is via veth pairs.

This patch enables the use of openvswitch patch-ports for local, flat and
vlan deployments with a fall back to veth pairs in the eventuality
patch-ports are not supported.

Implements blueprint openvswitch-patch-port-use

Change-Id: I70376c74e18c718f48c9d4caadaaf80c0095fc74

commit_message:
Fix misnamed baremetal state DELETED

* The baremetal state "DELETED" actually indicates that node is powered
  off, hence introducing a appropriate state "POWER_OFF" to indicate the
  same, instead of "DELETED" which is confusing.

Change-Id: I396425f7c127366b0fa66125ba5a96c3b7f633f9
Closes-Bug: #1185081

commit_message:
Fixes v2 return status on unauthorized download

If a user is not allowed to download an image because of a policy,
glance v2 API responds with a  HTTP 200 status and no data instead
of HTTP 403 for no cache only.
The problem is that get_data implementation for notification
proxy is a generator, this situation delays the other proxies
get_data calls (including the policy proxy) for the first time
data is retrieved.
Hence, there is a delay in enforcing policy, so 200 is sent before
the API gets the chance to catch the policy exception.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1326781
Change-Id: I1e50a069a6b7f9eed7160cd5908a5fa30274e227

commit_message:
Corrects proxy server conf in swift install guide

The install and configuration guide for object storage has
proxy-server.conf contents with /home/swift/keystone-signing as
signing directory. Without the directory being available swift proxy
service is unable to start. Signing directory is a temporary cache
directory which defaults to /tmp. Hence removing this entry makes
/tmp as default signing directory. This patch removes signing_dir
option to make swift use /tmp as signing directory implicitly.

Change-Id: I8b9b70b30af2767f48705acb14329833179b96fc
Closes-Bug: #1329798

commit_message:
Update websocketproxy to work with websockify 0.6

Websockify version 0.6 bring with it several bugfixes
and new features that affect Nova (including a fix for
novncproxy zombies hanging around and better support
for the python logging framework).  However, it also
broke backwards compatibility due to a refactor which
brought it inline with other Python socket server libraries.

This patch updates the websockify code to function with
websockify version 0.6 as well as websockify version 0.5.x.

Change-Id: I7858dbb49bee8de3fe725beb6793eac3ecba71b6

commit_message:
virt: Let six.moves.urllib to handle urllib/urllib2

Though nova hasn't the road map of Python 3 compatibility, it's not a
good practice of using six.moves.urllib with urllib/urllib2 together.
This commit unifies the urllib related usage in virt directory.
For usage of six.moves.urllib, please refer to
https://pythonhosted.org/six/#module-six.moves.urllib.parse

Change-Id: Ifc568b964a6ec815139b433c0089ed41c7e7abf5

commit_message:
Destroy instance to clear node state on failure

After a node has failed to deploy an instance, ensure the instance is
destroyed from the virt driver.  This clears the node state entirely before
the instance gets rescheduled.

Change-Id: I6a5d04f4c26c0910274783c0f686b0542af15f9c
Closes-bug: #1326364.

commit_message:
Clean nova.compute.api.API:_check_num_instances_quota

Simplification to a better understanding of total_allowed value

total_allowed = used + headroom [resource]
with used = quotas [resource] - headroom [resource]

commit_message:
properly quote www-authenticate header value

HTTP header values should be quoted. Since the WWW-Authenticate
header value contains user-supplied strings, it's important to
ensure it's properly quoted to ensure the integrity of the protocol.

Previous to this patch, the URL was unquoted and then the unquoted
value was returned in the header. This patch re-quotes the value
when it is set on the response.

This is filed as CVS-2014-3497

Fixes bug 1327414

Change-Id: If8bd8842f2ce821756e9b4461a18a8ac8d42fb8c

commit_message:
Fix the duplicated image params in a test

In _test_create, there is a parameter "no_image" to disable "image_ref"
in a request body of "create a server" API. The way of disabling is
setting '' as "image_ref".
So the unit tests using _test_create pass the duplicated images:
the parameter image_ref '' and the parameter block_device_mapping

This patch fixes this duplicated image parameters.
This problem was detected through the API validation works and
Ic17d2227909c9180ca86c9d578dad4c73ec57dfc needs this fixing.

Change-Id: I36ffc87309afadec7da3fa19e01ea8f00f0f9f8d

commit_message:
Add task/flow listener support around the volume api flow

This will add in logging of what is occurring around the
actions taken by taskflow when taskflow executes the initial
create_volume workflow.

Since the oslo logging module will include the request_id of
the currently active request (per greenthread) this will make
it easier to understand and debug the actions occurring inside
taskflow's engine concept.

Part of blueprint task-logging

Change-Id: I57a6f85ecac37fc4f97033eb3b7a0dc8bd35a886

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-06-10 22:25:30.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/test.py'], 'message': 'Fix log capturing fixture

Instead of nuking the unit test logs capture them according
to how tempest (and oslotest) capture them so that the tests
when ran locally provide the full logging output instead of
a miniaturized version.

This adds in the following environment variables which can
be used to control testr captured logging:

- OS_LOG_CAPTURE (turns on log capturing so that the testr
  repository will have log output, at a INFO level)
- OS_DEBUG (changes the captured logging level from INFO
  to DEBUG, only useful when OS_LOG_CAPTURE is enabled)

It also creates a lambda that is used to test whether an

of checks in multiple places).

Change-Id: I63d9a1b7fc6e7591fd6309cf68d9269117c023a6
'}]
commit_message:
Fix log capturing fixture

Instead of nuking the unit test logs capture them according
to how tempest (and oslotest) capture them so that the tests
when ran locally provide the full logging output instead of
a miniaturized version.

This adds in the following environment variables which can
be used to control testr captured logging:

- OS_LOG_CAPTURE (turns on log capturing so that the testr
  repository will have log output, at a INFO level)
- OS_DEBUG (changes the captured logging level from INFO
  to DEBUG, only useful when OS_LOG_CAPTURE is enabled)

It also creates a lambda that is used to test whether an
environment is enabled (avoiding recreating the same set
of checks in multiple places).

Change-Id: I63d9a1b7fc6e7591fd6309cf68d9269117c023a6

commit_message:
Support keystone v3 api

Keystone API v2 is deprecated in Icehouse. All projects client
need to switch to v3 API at end of Juno. We should add v3
support in python-cinderclient.

Change-Id: If7459df9bdf117435f271b46f2a8535d873cfdde
Implements: blueprint support-keystone-v3-api

commit_message:
Add doc8 a documentation style checking package

Many of the projects are starting to do style checks
on there specs files or other rst files so it seems
appropriate to use a small utility library to do these
kinds of checks (to avoid repeated copied code).

Doc8 starts to create a path for a common rst documentation
checking suite that can avoid the 'test_titles.py' tests
that are appearing in the various specification repositories.

Projects that currently can benefit from this package:

- TaskFlow
- Cinder
- Others with spec repos (nova, glance, oslo...)
 
Change-Id: Ie942497d88ad4dc9a4b3e58bea213354ec5513c5

commit_message:
Fix "fixed_ip" parameters in unit tests

In test_create_instance_with_neutronv2_fixed_ip_already_in_use of both
v2 and v3, these tests pass wrong parameters "fixed-ip" instead of
valid parameter "fixed_ip".
The purposes of these tests are to check the behaviors when passing
in-use addresses, but current tests contain two negative factors and
we cannot test the purposes now.

This patch fixes the parameters. This problem was detected through the
API validation works and Ic17d2227909c9180ca86c9d578dad4c73ec57dfc needs
this fixing.

Change-Id: I4d54a1522983c996431b995ed157b32d13c3bc88
Closes-Bug: #1331317

commit_message:
Correct node erase sequence

This sequence is more accurate as it sends SIGTERM to all processes.

- Send SIGTERM to all processes
- Trap SIGTERM
- Sync and set RO flag on all partitions
- Erase bootable partitions with dd
- Send "b" to sysrq-trigger

Closes-Bug: 1268641
Closes-Bug: 1279720

Change-Id: I4eaa6ed9b2872f55efaff0a874ac280bdba02226
(cherry picked from commit 694b5a55695e01e1c42185bfac9cc7a641a9bd48)

commit_message:
Removes the use of mutables as default args

Passing mutable objects as default args is a known Python pitfall.
We'd better avoid this. This commit changes mutable default args with
None, then use 'arg = arg or {}', 'arg = arg or []'. For unit code which
doesn't use the args , just set with None. This commit also adds hacking
check.

Closes-Bug: #1327473
Change-Id: I5a8492bf8ffef8e000b13b6bdfaef1968b96f816

[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-06-17 11:20:30.000000000', 'files': ['nova/objects/base.py', 'nova/tests/objects/test_objects.py'], 'message': "Initialize objects field in ObjectsListBase class

Normally the underlying value of an object attribute is set upon first
attempt to set it and would not exist otherwise. This causes the object
attribute access mechanism to fall back to obj_load_attr.

This is mostly fine for a lot of use cases, but it also means that for
ObjectListBase subclasses, it is not possible to construct them empty
and then call list methods on them without resorting to something like:

commit_message:
Initialize objects field in ObjectsListBase class

Normally the underlying value of an object attribute is set upon first
attempt to set it and would not exist otherwise. This causes the object
attribute access mechanism to fall back to obj_load_attr.

This is mostly fine for a lot of use cases, but it also means that for
ObjectListBase subclasses, it is not possible to construct them empty
and then call list methods on them without resorting to something like:

  myListObject(objects=[])

This patch makes ObjectListBase default it's objects filed to [] if it's
not passed in allowing us to have a cleaner API and call list methods
such as len() on objects constructed on the fly..

Change-Id: Iad1301cc4f88018f10f3dd6c76e35275cd0c51f6

commit_message:
Remove bdms from run_instance RPC conductor call

After the move to build_and_run_instance in change
Iefab71047996b7cc08107794d5bc628c11680a70 we get the block device
mapping out from the DB on the conductor side. We need to do this since
there is not enough data in the RPC call from the API (we don't have DB
id's so compute can't use that data to update block devices in the boot
process).

Based on this - we should stop sending block devices to the conductor.

Change-Id: Ic7a5da3f0d58093c3b249025b9fcd36a1321f2b3

commit_message:
Splits hbase storage code base

The hbase storage file have three different kind of things
* The Connection class
* The In-Memory implementation of HBase
* The a list of helper methods

This change splits this three things into separate files

Partial implements blueprint dedicated-alarm-database
Co-Authored-By: Ala Rezmerita <ala.rezmerita@cloudwatt.com>

commit_message:
Prefix database parameters with database_ for consistency

Although database configurations were moved to the new database
section, parameters were not renamed accordingly.

This change renames those parameter for consistency with the other
modules and actual database configuration names.

Conflicts:
  manifests/init.pp

HTTP header values should be quoted. Since the WWW-Authenticate
header value contains user-supplied strings, it's important to
ensure it's properly quoted to ensure the integrity of the protocol.

Previous to this patch, the URL was unquoted and then the unquoted
value was returned in the header. This patch re-quotes the value
when it is set on the response.

This is filed as CVS-2014-3497

Fixes bug 1327414

Change-Id: If8bd8842f2ce821756e9b4461a18a8ac8d42fb8c
"}]
commit_message:
properly quote www-authenticate header value

HTTP header values should be quoted. Since the WWW-Authenticate
header value contains user-supplied strings, it's important to
ensure it's properly quoted to ensure the integrity of the protocol.

Previous to this patch, the URL was unquoted and then the unquoted
value was returned in the header. This patch re-quotes the value
when it is set on the response.

This is filed as CVS-2014-3497

Fixes bug 1327414

Change-Id: If8bd8842f2ce821756e9b4461a18a8ac8d42fb8c

commit_message:
Add unit tests for ipv4/ipv6 format validation

We found a bug that the other jsonschema format check('uri') did
not work for input validation. There was not any unit tests for
the format check, then we could not find it in long term.
The bug is fixed with Ibb2b7f27c374136e6865b28786d10ca1365e5709 .
And this patch adds unit tests for the format 'ipv4' and 'ipv6'.

Change-Id: I6f6636708e3f9a4eee14451f2baacb50002f1db8
Related-Bug: #1326599

commit_message:
TripleO on OpenStack

A specification describing the work needed to enable doing TripleO
development on OpenStack instances instead of using virsh directly.

Large scale tests of TripleO require more resources than can be
obtained on a single machine using virsh emulated baremetal
machines. Rather than invest in this adhoc solution, making
OpenStack be able to deliver a robust emulated baremetal
environment spanning multiple hypervisors will permit efficient
at-scale tests.

Change-Id: Idb94f2eb37a59780633fb4428f3b402b3bb6bfca
Partial-Blueprint: tripleo-on-openstack
